{"title_page": "Velleia lyrata", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{speciesbox\n|image = Flower Velleia lyrata, (Goodeniaceae).jpg\n|image_caption = \n|genus = Velleia\n|species = lyrata\n|authority = [[R.Br.]]<ref name=Brown/><ref name=APNI/>\n|range_map=VelleialyrataDistributionMap14.png \n|range_map_caption=Occurrence data from [[Australasian Virtual Herbarium|AVH]]\n}}\n'''''Velleia lyrata''''' is a small perennial herb in the family [[Goodeniaceae]], [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Australia]]. It is found mainly near [[Sydney]], but also near the [[New South Wales|NSW]] and [[Queensland]] border, and in Queensland.<ref name=Plantnet/><ref name=AVHmap/> A map of its occurrence records is given [http://avh.ala.org.au/occurrences/search?taxa=Velleia+lyrata#tab_mapView here.] It grows in damp situations in heath on sandy soils.<ref name=Plantnet/> \nThe cordate base to the adaxial sepal is a feature distinguishing it from many other [[Velleia]]s.<ref name=FloraAustOnline/> A full description of the plant is given in [http://www.anbg.gov.au/abrs/online-resources/flora/stddisplay.xsql?pnid=50017 Flora of Australia online].\n\nThe species was first described as ''Velleia lyrata'' by the [[botanist]] [[Robert Brown (botanist, born 1773)|Robert Brown]] in 1810 <ref name=Brown/><ref name=APNI/> and the name has never been revised.<ref name=APNI/>\n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using<ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=APNI>{{cite web|url=https://biodiversity.org.au/nsl/services/name/apni/70127/api/apni-format |title=Australian Plant Name Index(APNI): ''Velleia lyrata''.}} IBIS database. Centre for Plant Biodiversity Research, Australian Government, Canberra. Accessed 1 April 2018.</ref>\n<ref name=Plantnet>{{Cite web|url=http://plantnet.rbgsyd.nsw.gov.au/cgi-bin/NSWfl.pl?page=nswfl&lvl=sp&name=Velleia~lyrata|title=Velleia lyrata R.Br.|website=PlantNET \u2013 FloraOnline|publisher=National Herbarium of NSW|access-date=2018-04-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=AVHmap>{{Cite web|url=http://avh.ala.org.au/occurrences/search?taxa=Velleia+lyrata#tab_mapView|title=Velleria lyrata Occurrence records|website=The Australasian Virtual Herbarium|publisher=Council of Heads of Australasian Herbaria|language=en-AU|access-date=2018-04-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=Brown>Brown, R. (1810) {{cite book|url=https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2954736 |title=Prodromus florae Novae Hollandiae et insulae Van-Diemen, exhibens characteres plantarum quas annis 1802-1805: 580|publisher=typis R. Taylor et socii|year=1810}}</ref> \n<ref name=FloraAustOnline>{{cite web|url=http://www.anbg.gov.au/abrs/online-resources/flora/stddisplay.xsql?pnid=50017 |title=Flora of Australia online:''Velleia lyrata''.|author=Carolin, R.C}} Data derived from Flora of Australia Volume 35 (1992), ABRS, \u00a9Commonwealth of Australia. Accessed April 1, 2018.</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://avh.ala.org.au/occurrences/search?taxa=Velleia+lyrata#tab_mapView The Australasian Virtual Herbarium \u2013 Distribution]\n* [http://plantnet.rbgsyd.nsw.gov.au/cgi-bin/NSWfl.pl?page=nswfl&lvl=sp&name=Velleia~lyrata PlantNET \u2013 Description]\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q17480527}}\n\n[[Category:Flora of Queensland]]\n[[Category:Flora of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Velleia|lyrata]]\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{speciesbox\n|image = Flower Velleia lyrata, (Goodeniaceae).jpg\n|image_caption = \n|genus = Velleia\n|species = lyrata\n|authority = [[R.Br.]]<ref name=Brown/><ref name=APNI/>\n|range_map=VelleialyrataDistributionMap14.png \n|range_map_caption=Occurrence data from [[Australasian Virtual Herbarium|AVH]]\n}}\n'''''Velleia lyrata''''' is a small perennial herb in the [[Goodeniaceae]] family, [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Australia]]. It is found mainly near [[Sydney]], but also near the [[New South Wales|NSW]] and [[Queensland]] border, and in Queensland.<ref name=Plantnet/><ref name=AVHmap/> A map of its occurrence records is given [http://avh.ala.org.au/occurrences/search?taxa=Velleia+lyrata#tab_mapView here.] It grows in damp situations in heath on sandy soils.<ref name=Plantnet/> \nThe cordate base to the adaxial sepal is a feature distinguishing it from many other [[Velleia|Velleias]].<ref name=FloraAustOnline/> A full description of the plant is given in [http://www.anbg.gov.au/abrs/online-resources/flora/stddisplay.xsql?pnid=50017 Flora of Australia online].\n\nThe species was first described as ''Velleia lyrata'' by the [[botanist]] [[Robert Brown (botanist, born 1773)|Robert Brown]] in 1810 <ref name=Brown/><ref name=APNI/> and the name has never been revised.<ref name=APNI/>. \n\n== References ==\n<!--- See http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Footnotes on how to create references using<ref></ref> tags, these references will then appear here automatically -->\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=APNI>{{cite web|url=https://biodiversity.org.au/nsl/services/name/apni/70127/api/apni-format |title=Australian Plant Name Index(APNI): ''Velleia lyrata''.}} IBIS database. Centre for Plant Biodiversity Research, Australian Government, Canberra. Accessed 1 April 2018.</ref>\n<ref name=Plantnet>{{Cite web|url=http://plantnet.rbgsyd.nsw.gov.au/cgi-bin/NSWfl.pl?page=nswfl&lvl=sp&name=Velleia~lyrata|title=Velleia lyrata R.Br.|website=PlantNET \u2013 FloraOnline|publisher=National Herbarium of NSW|access-date=2018-04-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=AVHmap>{{Cite web|url=http://avh.ala.org.au/occurrences/search?taxa=Velleia+lyrata#tab_mapView|title=Velleria lyrata Occurrence records|website=The Australasian Virtual Herbarium|publisher=Council of Heads of Australasian Herbaria|language=en-AU|access-date=2018-04-01}}</ref>\n<ref name=Brown>Brown, R. (1810) {{cite book|url=https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/2954736 |title=Prodromus florae Novae Hollandiae et insulae Van-Diemen, exhibens characteres plantarum quas annis 1802-1805: 580|publisher=typis R.